ame\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σώσι Νύμφων\n                    Κραφάγε\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σώσι\">Σώσι\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Νύμφων\">Νύμφων\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Κραφάγε\">Κραφάγε\u003C/span>\u003C/span> χαῖρε \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σώσι Νύμφων\n                    Κραφάγε\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σώσι\">ΣΩΣΙ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Νύμφων\">ΝΥΜΦΩΝ\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Κραφάγε\">ΚΡΑΦΑΓΕ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>ΧΑΙΡΕ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001173_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic001173_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001173.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic001173-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001173_text_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic001173_text_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001173_text.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic001173_text-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001173_context_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic001173_context_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001173_context.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic001173_context-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Sosis Nymphon 'the meat-eater', farewell!\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>SEG 37.763 reports the observation of Masson that Κραφάγε should be an epithet, meaning 'eater of meat'. Νύμφων is either the patronymic (in which case the genitive ending has either been omitted, or the right edge of the stone was trimmed for re-use in the church wall), or else a second name in the Sicilian fashion, with Κραφάγε then an additional epithet.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 58.1045 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> 37.0763 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Franz 1853 5593 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">351\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1965 200 tav. 72.1 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001841\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001841\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Tullio 1974 131 n. 70 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002336\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002336\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Arena 1987 14-15 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002335\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002335\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Brugnone 2005 849 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002116\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002116\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Montalbano 2008 177 VS 4 tav. 33.3 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001740\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001740\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Somewhat crude, large letters, probably later Hellenistic: sigma has parallel top and bottom strokes; omega is closed, tending to elliptical in form; mu has vertical first and last strokes, mid-point descends half-way only; phi has small circular eye and extended vertical; kappa has short tails; alpha has broken bar; epsilon has short middle stroke\u003C/p> Line 1  85  Line 2  75-80  Interlineation line 1 to 2  10-15  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  \u003C/div>",[264,267,270,273,276,279,282,285],{"id":265,"html":266},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σώσι Νύμφων\n                    Κραφάγε\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σώσι\">Σώσι\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Νύμφων\">Νύμφων\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Κραφάγε\">Κραφάγε\u003C/span>\u003C/span> χαῖρε \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σώσι Νύμφων\n                    Κραφάγε\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σώσι\">ΣΩΣΙ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Νύμφων\">ΝΥΜΦΩΝ\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Κραφάγε\">ΚΡΑΦΑΓΕ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>ΧΑΙΡΕ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":268,"html":269},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001173_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic001173_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001173.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic001173-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001173_text_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic001173_text_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001173_text.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic001173_text-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001173_context_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic001173_context_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001173_context.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"Photo J. Prag\" src=\"ISic001173_context-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":271,"html":272},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":274,"html":275},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Sosis Nymphon 'the meat-eater', farewell!\u003C/p>  ",{"id":277,"html":278},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>SEG 37.763 reports the observation of Masson that Κραφάγε should be an epithet, meaning 'eater of meat'. Νύμφων is either the patronymic (in which case the genitive ending has either been omitted, or the right edge of the stone was trimmed for re-use in the church wall), or else a second name in the Sicilian fashion, with Κραφάγε then an additional epithet.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":280,"html":281},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> 58.1045 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> 37.0763 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000796\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Franz 1853 5593 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">351\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manganaro 1965 200 tav. 72.1 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001841\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001841\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Tullio 1974 131 n. 70 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002336\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002336\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Arena 1987 14-15 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002335\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002335\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Brugnone 2005 849 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002116\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002116\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Montalbano 2008 177 VS 4 tav. 33.3 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001740\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001740\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":283,"html":284},"handnote","\u003Cp>Somewhat crude, large letters, probably later Hellenistic: sigma has parallel top and bottom strokes; omega is closed, tending to elliptical in form; mu has vertical first and last strokes, mid-point descends half-way only; phi has small circular eye and extended vertical; kappa has short tails; alpha has broken bar; epsilon has short middle stroke\u003C/p> Line 1  85  Line 2  75-80  Interlineation line 1 to 2  10-15  ",{"id":286,"html":287},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.  ",[289,291,294,295],{"html":290},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag",{"id":292,"lang":120,"html":293},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Σώσι Νύμφων\n                    Κραφάγε\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Σώσι\">Σώσι\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Νύμφων\">Νύμφων\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Κραφάγε\">Κραφάγε\